Try Out XCP-ng Hypervisor in VirtualBox
NOTE: This is a helpful exercise to get familiar with the XCP-ng user interface and terminology but is not recommended for production use.

Download the XCP-ng .iso file Download
Launch Virtualbox
Create a New VM by selecting Machine > New
Name: XCP-ng
Machine Folder: C:\VMs
Type: Linux
Version: Other (64-bit)
Memory Size: 8192 MB
Hard disk: Create a virtual hard disk now

Click Create
On the Create Virtual Hard Disk dialog
Name the virtual disk image XCP-ng.vdi
File size: 120 GB
Hard disk file type: VDI
Storage on physical hard disk: Dynamically Allocated

Click Create
Select the VM and Click Settings
Select System > Processor
Give the VM at least 2 processors
Check the Enable Nested VT-x/AMD-V
Select Display
Slide the Video Memory to 128 MB
Select Network
Set the attached to dropdown to Bridged Adapter
Select Storage
Click on the CD-ROM drive
Select the disc dropdown to the right > Choose a virtual optical disc file...
Browse to and select the downloaded XCP-ng .iso file
Click OK
Select the hard disk dropdown to the right
Click the Create button at the top
Change the size to 500 GB > Click Create
Click OK to accept the settings
Make sure the XCP-ng VM is selected and click Start > Normal
Press Enter to begin the installation
Select a keyboard mapping > Ok
Select OK at the welcome screen > Press Enter
Select Accept EULA > Press Enter
Make sure the VBOX HARDDISK is selected > Tab to select Ok > Press Enter
Select Local Media > Tab to select Ok > Press Enter
Select Skip verification > Tab to select Ok > Press Enter
Enter and confirm a root password
Configure the network > Ok
Specify a hostname > Ok
Select a Geographic area > Ok
Set the time zone > Ok
Select Using NTP > Ok
Select Ok at the NTP server setup
Select Install XPC-ng
Select No at the supplemental packs installation screen
After the installation completes, select Devices > Optical Drives > Remove disk from virtual drive
Select Ok to reboot
Welcome to XPC-ng
Installing Xen Orchestra Web UI
Arrow down to Network and Management Interface
Note the IP address displayed
Open a web browser and navigate to http:// IP address of XPC-ng
Click the Quick Deploy button under Xen Orchestra
Enter the password set during the installation process > Click Connect
Click the Next button
Set the web UI admin username and password
Set the XOA machine password
Click Deploy
 
